My goal for 2022 was to be intentional about creating meaningful experiences with people that I truly wanted to be around and all I can say is mission accomplished! It was a year where things fell into place without me forcing them. I've been blessed in ways that I wouldn't have thought to ask & my spirit is full. Thank everyone who had a hand in making this year special. I'm grateful for all that we shared together; the memories, the lessons learned & the thrill of the creative process! Happy New Year!

During the month of April, I was on the road to rest & reflection (see my March Recap video to understand why). I made self-care my top priority & it started with a silent retreat at a small cabin in the wooded mountains of Pennsylvania. As an introvert, that time to myself was the recharge that I needed. Other kinds of self-care I engaged in throughout the month included journaling, regular exercise, long motorcycle rides, massage therapy, creative projects, reducing the number of bookings I accepted during the month of April & finally learning the ancient practice of Transcendental Meditation (TM). All of that to say, I'm feeling & thinking like a new man. Time to get back to work...
#kelbpics #selfcare #igreels

Slide 3: @dcyoungfly going over his lines in his dressing room

Slide 4: @tichinaarnold enjoying a laugh before hitting the stage for the "Hey Ladies" comedy show

Slide 5: @therealtommycat meeting @yvonneorji for the first time, as @joeclair looks on

Slide 7: A surprise visit from @therealchrisspencer & @tony_rock
